## Test Naming Convention

```
test_<component>_<scenario>_<expected_outcome>
```

Examples:
- `test_rsi_strategy_overbought_returns_sell`
- `test_portfolio_buy_insufficient_cash_raises`
- `test_alpaca_provider_missing_symbol_returns_err`
- `test_signal_engine_tie_vote_holds`

---

## Do Not

- ❌ Test private methods directly — test observable behavior
- ❌ Assert on log output as the primary signal of correctness
- ❌ Sleep in unit tests — if timing matters, mock `datetime.utcnow`
- ❌ Share mutable state between test functions (no module-level portfolios)
- ❌ Write a test that only passes when Alpaca is live
